And what is Canada's Longest Community Name ...? Try ....

Cape St. George-Petit Jardin-Grand Jardin-De Grau-Marches Point-Loretto

(a small community in Newfoundland)

Canada's Longest Place Name is either L'Annonciation de la Bienheureuse Vierge Marie de Nazareth (which is a geographical area in Quebec and when translated from French to English is: The Annunciation of the Blessed Virgin Mary of Nazareth). - or - Pekwachnamaykoskwaskwaypinwanik (which is a lake in Manitoba and Nunavut).
